<i>noun</i>: 호전적 [호ː전적], 적의 [저긔/저기], 적대심 [적때심], 적대감 [적때감], 적개심 [적깨심], 반항심 [반ː항심], 반목 [반ː목], 반감 [반ː감] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>호전적 [호ː전적]</dt><br>
<dd>belligerence; hostility; aggression</dd><br>
<dd>싸우기를 좋아하는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of being inclined to fight.</dd><br>
<dt>적의 [저긔/저기]</dt><br>
<dd>1. hostility</dd><br>
<dd>적으로 대하는 마음.</dd><br>
<dd>An attitude that treats someone as an enemy.</dd><br>
<dd>2. hostility</dd><br>
<dd>해치려는 마음.</dd><br>
<dd>An intention to hurt someone.</dd><br>
<dt>적대심 [적때심]</dt><br>
<dd>hostility</dd><br>
<dd>적이나 그와 같은 대상으로 대하는 마음.</dd><br>
<dd>The sentiment of treating someone as an enemy or something similar.</dd><br>
<dt>적대감 [적때감]</dt><br>
<dd>hostility</dd><br>
<dd>적이나 그와 같은 대상으로 대하는 감정.</dd><br>
<dd>The sentiment of treating someone as an enemy or something similar.</dd><br>
<dt>적개심 [적깨심]</dt><br>
<dd>hostility</dd><br>
<dd>적이나 상대를 깊이 미워하여 분하게 여기거나 싸우고 싶어 하는 마음.</dd><br>
<dd>The attitude of resenting or wanting to fight against one's enemy or opponent due to deep hatred.</dd><br>
<dt>반항심 [반ː항심]</dt><br>
<dd>rebelliousness; hostility</dd><br>
<dd>다른 사람이나 대상에 맞서 달려들거나 부딪히려는 마음.</dd><br>
<dd>An urge to confront, attack or collide with another person or object.</dd><br>
<dt>반목 [반ː목]</dt><br>
<dd>enmity; hostility; antagonism</dd><br>
<dd>서로 시기하고 미워함.</dd><br>
<dd>The feeling of hating and envying each other.</dd><br>
<dt>반감 [반ː감]</dt><br>
<dd>hostility; antagonism; animosity</dd><br>
<dd>반대하거나 반항하는 감정.</dd><br>
<dd>A feeling of opposition or defiance.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>